The paper deals with a graph optimization problem, specifically the Tree Augmentation Problem (TAP), which involves finding a minimum set of edges to augment the edge connectivity of a graph from 1 to 2. This problem is related to topics in computer science such as graph theory (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), computational geometry (cs.CG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
